The Fitko App was Developped using React Native Technology for crossed platforms.

The main tasks achieved during the first commits were:
         Create a first design template for the application's front end.
         Mainly the libraries that were used are:
          React Navigation to navigate through different screens.
          React Native Gesture Handler to create scrollable screen
          React Native Swipers to swipe through the activities demonstative photos
 The remaining tasks consitsts of:
         Connecting the backend using React Native BluetoothSerial library
         Enabling the Bluetooth pairing API & Establishing the connection between
         the ESP32 and the React Native App.
         
          
